{{unreferenced|date=January 2017}}
[[File:Estonian archipelago (Saaremaa and Hiiumaa).jpg|300px|thumb|The Gulf of Riga, with Irbe Strait on the left of the map]]
'''Irbe Strait''', also known as '''Irben Strait''' ({{lang-et|Kura kurk}}, {{lang-lv|Irbes jūras šaurums}}, {{lang-liv|Sūr mer}}), forms the main exit out of the [[Gulf of Riga]] to the [[Baltic Sea]], between the [[Sõrve Peninsula]] forming the southern end of the island [[Saaremaa]] in [[Estonia]] and [[Courland Peninsula]] in [[Latvia]]. It is {{cvt|27|km}} wide at its narrowest point. A shipping channel has been [[dredging|dredged]] along its southern shore to allow larger ships to pass.

See also [[Saunags]].

