'''Oluf van Steenwinckel''' (died 1659) was a [[Denmark|Danish]] building master and engineer, probably the son of [[Hans van Steenwinckel the Younger]]. In the 1640s he worked at Nykøbing Castle among other places and from 1651-52 he was Copenhagen's first City Surveyor (Danish: Stadskonduktør), involved in the [[Cadastre|cedestral]] registration and parcelling of [[Frederick III of Denmark|Frederick III]]'s ''[[Kongens Nytorv#History|New Copenhagen]].'' In June 1659, during the [[Northern Wars]], he participated in a failed attempt to recapture [[Kronborg Castle]] and was [[Capital punishment|executed]] by the Swedish.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.denstoredanske.dk/Kunst_og_kultur/Arkitektur/Ren%C3%A6ssance/Oluf_van_Steenwinckel|title=Oluf van Steenwinckel|language=Danish|publisher=Gyldendal|accessdate=2010-01-03}}</ref>
==See also== * [[Hans van Steenwinckel the Younger|Hans van Steenwinckel]]
