'''Tannochbrae''' is a fictional village in [[Scotland]] first introduced in the [[Dr. Finley]] short stories of [[A. J. Cronin]] as a "snug little village on the lochside", and later used in his autobiographical ''Adventures in Two Worlds''.  It is best known as the setting of the television and radio series based Cronin's Dr. Finley stories. <ref>[https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0853494/ "Dr. Finlay's Casebook" The Phantom Piper of Tannochbrae (TV episode 1965)] – IMDb</ref>

The filming of the original [[BBC]] series, ''[[Dr. Finlay's Casebook (TV & radio)|Dr Finlay's Casebook]]'', took place in [[Callander]].  The second [[ITV Network|ITV]] series, ''[[Doctor Finlay]]'', was filmed in [[Auchtermuchty]].

